-- Real Madrid Rallies Past Mallorca to Extend Spanish Soccer Lead
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-14T22:50:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-14/real-madrid-rallies-past-mallorca-to-extend-spanish-soccer-lead.html
Real Madrid came from behind to
defeat  Mallorca  2-1 and extend its lead in Spanish soccer’s
Primera Division to eight points over Barcelona.  Thomer Hemed gave Mallorca the lead in the first half
before Real’s Gonzalo Higuain tied the score in the 72nd minute.
Jose Maria Callejon then got the winning goal with six minutes
remaining.  Paris Saint-Germain beat Toulouse 3-1 to maintin its three-
point lead in france’s Ligue 1 over Montpellier, which defeated
Lyon 1-0. It was the first league match for PSG manager  Carlo
Ancelotti , who was hired Dec. 30 to replace Antoine Kombouare.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
